Governor Aminu Masari of Katsina State has expressed satisfaction with the smooth conduct of the Presidential and National Assembly elections in the state. Masari disclosed this after casting his vote on Saturday at Masari ward in Kafur Local Government Area of the state. He said that the election was being conducted in an orderly manner devoid of rancour and violence. “We have to thank Allah for bringing us to this important day in the lives of Nigerians who are out to elect new leaders. “We are calling on Nigerians to maintain the peaceful and orderly manner the election is going on, in order to achieve the desired goal,” he said.